{% doc %}

  Collection filter drawer (mobile)
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Full-screen slide-in drawer that contains all `collection.filters`, stacked
  as `<details>` accordion sections. Uses the shared `.drawer` primitive.

  Must be rendered INSIDE the collection toolbar `<form>` so its inputs are
  included on submit alongside the desktop pill inputs.

  On desktop the drawer is never opened (the desktop pill row is the UI), so
  we render the drawer markup only on mobile breakpoints via CSS.

  @example
    {% render 'collection-filter-drawer' %}

{% enddoc %}

<div
  id="collection-filter-drawer"
  class="drawer collection-filter-drawer lg:hidden"
  data-component="collection-filter-drawer"
  aria-hidden="true"
  role="dialog"
  aria-labelledby="collection-filter-drawer-title"
  inert
>
  <div class="collection-filter-drawer__inner" data-scroller>
    <header class="collection-filter-drawer__header">
      <span id="collection-filter-drawer-title" class="collection-filter-drawer__title">{{ 'collections.filters.title' | t }}</span>
      <button
        type="button"
        class="collection-filter-drawer__close"
        data-close
        aria-label="{{ 'general.close' | t }}"
      >&times;</button>
    </header>

    {%- comment -%}
      Drawer groups use the shared `.collapsible` / `.collapsible-toggle`
      primitive (same as the PDP info accordion) so both surfaces share
      one 500ms grid-rows animation matching CLAUDE.md's standard.
      Earlier iteration used native `<details>` which has no built-in
      expand/collapse animation across browsers.

      Groups default to open when their filter has active values, so
      users land on the state that reflects what's already applied.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="collection-filter-drawer__body">
      {% for f in collection.filters %}
        {%- liquid
          assign has_active = false
          if f.active_values.size > 0
            assign has_active = true
          endif
          if f.type == 'price_range'
            if f.min_value.value or f.max_value.value
              assign has_active = true
            endif
          endif
          assign drawer_panel_id = 'drawer-filter-' | append: forloop.index
          assign drawer_toggle_id = drawer_panel_id | append: '-toggle'
        -%}
        <div class="collection-filter-drawer__group">
          <button
            type="button"
            id="{{ drawer_toggle_id }}"
            class="collapsible-toggle collection-filter-drawer__group-title"
            aria-expanded="{% if has_active %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
            aria-controls="{{ drawer_panel_id }}"
            data-component="collapsible-toggle"
          >
            <span>{{ f.label }}</span>
            <span class="collection-filter-drawer__group-caret" aria-hidden="true" data-chevron>›</span>
          </button>
          <div
            id="{{ drawer_panel_id }}"
            class="collapsible{% if has_active %} is-open{% endif %}"
            role="region"
            aria-labelledby="{{ drawer_toggle_id }}"
          >
            <div class="collapsible__inner">
              <div class="collection-filter-drawer__group-body">
                {% render 'filter-values', filter: f %}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      {% endfor %}

      {%- comment -%}
        Sort accordion — lives inside the drawer on mobile instead of
        being a separate pill on the toolbar. Matches the filter-group
        markup + CSS so the drawer reads as one consistent list of
        collapsible sections.

        `name="sort_by"` is intentionally the same as the desktop sort
        pill's radios (see `sort-dropdown.liquid`): the browser treats
        them as one radio group and keeps selection in sync. On Apply,
        the form serializes whichever `sort_by` is currently checked
        and the page navigates to the new URL.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- liquid
        assign current_sort = collection.sort_by | default: collection.default_sort_by
        assign current_sort_label = ''
        for option in collection.sort_options
          if option.value == current_sort
            assign current_sort_label = option.name
            break
          endif
        endfor
        if current_sort_label == ''
          assign current_sort_label = collection.sort_options.first.name
        endif
      -%}
      <div class="collection-filter-drawer__group">
        <button
          type="button"
          id="drawer-sort-toggle"
          class="collapsible-toggle collection-filter-drawer__group-title"
          aria-expanded="false"
          aria-controls="drawer-sort-panel"
          data-component="collapsible-toggle"
        >
          <span>{{ 'collections.sort.label' | t }}: {{ current_sort_label }}</span>
          <span class="collection-filter-drawer__group-caret" aria-hidden="true" data-chevron>›</span>
        </button>
        <div
          id="drawer-sort-panel"
          class="collapsible"
          role="region"
          aria-labelledby="drawer-sort-toggle"
        >
          <div class="collapsible__inner">
            <div class="collection-filter-drawer__group-body">
              <ul class="collection-filter-drawer__values">
                {% for option in collection.sort_options %}
                  <li>
                    <label class="filter-value{% if option.value == current_sort %} filter-value--active{% endif %}">
                      <input
                        type="radio"
                        name="sort_by"
                        value="{{ option.value }}"
                        class="sr-only"
                        {% if option.value == current_sort %}checked{% endif %}
                      >
                      <span class="filter-value__label">{{ option.name }}</span>
                    </label>
                  </li>
                {% endfor %}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="collection-filter-drawer__footer">
      {%- comment -%}
        Apply submits the form as a full navigation — the drawer can't stay
        open across a DOM swap, and the AJAX path is only wired for desktop
        change-events. `CollectionToolbar.onSubmit` intercepts this
        submitter to build a deduped URL (native serialization would emit
        duplicate name+value pairs since filter inputs are rendered twice)
        and then navigates via `window.location.href`.

        Label is pre-assigned: Shopify's `render` tag doesn't evaluate
        filter chains on inline args, so `label: '...' | t` leaks the raw
        key through — the translation has to happen before the render call.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign apply_label = 'collections.filters.apply' | t -%}
      {% render 'button',
                label: apply_label,
                type: 'submit',
                variant: 'primary',
                size: 'lg',
                block: true
      %}
      <a href="{{ collection.url }}" class="collection-filter-drawer__clear" rel="nofollow">
        {{ 'collections.filters.clear_all' | t }}
      </a>
    </footer>
  </div>
</div>
